name: Minerva surveils the damage
description: In this handglitched, digitally handpainted auratic iconographic portrait, Greco-Roman goddess of war and wisdom Minerva-Athena surveils the sunset of a dying world. Her owl sits on the shield displaying Medusa the Gorgon’s mounted severed head. The poor Gorgon’s fabled frozen and freezing mien turns anything to stone with a mere glance. Minerva’s shield is also her greatest weapon.
